for your own personal transport, rural coaches are the only forms of transportation in many areas of china. on the bright side, such rural coaches are usually more than willing to stop anywhere along the route should you wish to visit more remote areas without direct transport. buses can also be flagged down at most points along their route. the ticket price the rest of the way is negotiable. everywhere in china drivers often disregard the rules of the road, if there are any, and accidents are frequent. sudden swerves and stops can cause injury, so keep a good hold 